Sources of data specific to the Greater Serengeti-Mara Ecosystem 


# Serengeti Animal Tracker #

https://serengeti-tracker.org/

(**Grant, struggling to get this website to load??**)


# Snapshot Serengeti #

https://snapshotserengeti.org/

Survey grid of 210 camera traps established in the Seronera region in 2010 by the Serengeti Lion Project (University of Minnesota). Includes identifications, counts, and behaviors of >40 Serengeti species. First three years of data publically available at https://datadryad.org/resource/doi:10.5061/dryad.5pt92 (contact: Meredith S. Palmer palme516@umn.edu) 


# Tanzanian Wildlife Research Institute (TAWIRI) #

http://tawiri.or.tz/

Tanzania Wildlife Research Institute is a parastatal organization under the Ministry of Natural Resources and Tourism responsible for conducting and coordinating wildlife research in the United Republic of Tanzania.


# Tanzanian National Parks Authority (TANAPA) #

http://www.tanzaniaparks.go.tz/

Tanzania National Parks manages the conservation of 16 national parks, including protection of natural resources, park management and development, ecological and wildlife health monitoring, tourism development, and community conservation. 


# Frankfurt Zoological Society (FZS) # 

https://fzs.org/en/projects/serengeti-conservation/

Frankfurt Zoological Society provides critical financial and logistical support and know-how for resource protection, ecological and threat monitoring and park management to the Serengeti National Park.
